reviews.text: Nice train station. Very clean except for a discarded McDonald's bag
Its a train station thats kind of it... Its small and very clean and the staff were great!
It's where I live and is an historic spa town

By far the finest railway station to be found the length and breadth of Droitwich. You can catch a train here from Droitwich Spa to Worcester or Birmingham and beyond. 

As if that wasn't enough, you can even catch another train to return you to this fine establishment. What more could anyone desire? 

I go here sometimes even when i'm not catching a train. That's how fantastic it is.

A pleasant rural station with a platform cafe kiosk and ticket office. When closed there are ticket machines. Waiting room and shelter, and bike racks. Plenty of parking paid and unpaid in the station vicinity.
